{
  "stem": "27443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at the time, one of my mother's brother came up to our house suggesting to my mother that he's going away to Bialystok, and he would like that my older brother should go with him.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in due time, maybe he could send somebody to bring our whole family and his, because he had a wife and two children too.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my mother was against it for my older brother to leave because she felt as long we are together as a family, maybe we have a chance of surviving.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But unfortunately proved no good because after the war, my uncle did survive in Russia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was pushed-- from Bialystok, he went into Russia and survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my older brother, I never saw him after the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He never survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prominent Jews from the city.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, as the war broke out, we lived in a court-- as I said, they were all orthodox Jews-- and in our court were five steibelach.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as soon the war broke out, we were afraid that they will burn just like they burned the synagogues.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the heads of the steibelach distributed all the Sefer torahs to all the Jewish people that lived in the court.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we also had a Sefer Torah in our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in fact, just before we were taken from our home, my father took one of the Sefer Torahs and put in a velvet bedspread and covered it.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
